# Language Standard (LT + EN)

This standard applies to every visible text agents touch: marketing copy in `src/content/copy.ts`, UI fallbacks in `src/components/**/*.astro`, the printable kit in `public/assets/downloads/`, and project documentation (`README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `docs/**/*.md`).

## Shared Principles

- Executive voice: decision, risk, trade-off, owner, next action, ROI.
- Forbidden vocabulary in marketing copy: "learn AI", "prompt engineering tutorial", "AI course", "beginner guide", "step-by-step intro".
- One idea per sentence. Cut adjectives that do not change meaning.
- EN and LT must stay aligned: when one section changes, update the other in the same edit.
- No emoji in landing copy unless explicitly requested by the user.
- Brand names stay verbatim: `PromptAnatomy`, `PromptAnatomy.app`, `Max Value Kit`, `Promptų anatomija`.

## Lithuanian Standard

### Address: always "Tu", never "Jūs"

Convert formal/plural imperatives to informal singular. The rule of thumb: drop the trailing `-ite`.

| Formal (do not use) | Informal (use this) |
|---|---|
| Pradėkite | Pradėk |
| Atsisiųskite | Atsisiųsk |
| Naudokite | Naudok |
| Pasiimkite | Pasiimk |
| Patikrinkite | Patikrink |
| Pasirinkite | Pasirink |
| Nesiųskite | Nesiųsk |
| Nukopijuokite | Nukopijuok |
| Paleiskite | Paleisk |
| Rašykite | Rašyk |
| Įdiekite | Įdiek |
| Peržiūrėkite | Peržiūrėk |
| Išgryninkite | Išgrynink |
| Paverskite | Paversk |
| Raskite | Surask |
| Ištraukite | Ištrauk |
| Atskirkite | Atskirk |
| jūsų | tavo |
| norite | nori |
| galite | gali |
| turite | turi |

Button labels use infinitive (neutral), not imperative: `Atsisiųsti`, `Pradėti praktiką`, `Kopijuoti promptą`. Do not turn buttons into "Tu" form.

Prompts addressed to the AI keep "Tu" form already: `Veik kaip...`, `Išanalizuok...`, `Sukurk...`, `Peržiūrėk...`, `Perrašyk...`. Do not change.

### AI → DI in Lithuanian

Always write `DI` (dirbtinis intelektas) in Lithuanian copy. The only place `AI` may appear is the English (`en`) block of `copy.ts`.

- `AI Operating System` → `DI operacinė sistema`
- `AI darbo eigos` ✗ already correct as `DI darbo eigos`
- Brand strings inside English fallbacks in `.astro` components stay `AI` because they are replaced at runtime.

### Diacritics are mandatory

Always: `ą č ę ė į š ų ū ž`. Reject ASCII fallbacks like `aciu`, `ka`, `kompromisas`. CI builds and screen readers depend on correct UTF-8.

### Preferred business vocabulary

| English | Use in LT | Avoid |
|---|---|---|
| trade-off | kompromisas | kompromisinis sprendimas |
| bottleneck | butelio kaklelis | siaura vieta |
| workflow | darbo eiga | darbo srautas, vorkflow |
| prompt | promptas | užklausa (when meaning the prompt artifact) |
| brief | briefas | (accepted in LT business jargon) |
| owner | savininkas | atsakingasis (only in legal context) |
| next action | kitas veiksmas | sekantis žingsnis |
| stakeholder | suinteresuota pusė | steikholderis |
| safety check | saugumo patikra | saugos check |
| support / account (CRM) | kliento aptarnavimas / paskyra | support / account (do not leave English) |

Loanwords already entrenched in LT business speech are acceptable: `briefas`, `promptas`, `checklist` (in code/UI labels), `lead magnet` (only inside marketing-jargon eyebrows). Do not introduce new anglicisms when a clean LT word exists.

### Punctuation

- Use the long dash `–` (en dash) for emphasis: `Problema – ne prieiga prie DI. Problema – kontrolė.`
- Lithuanian quotation marks `„..."` preferred in prose. `"..."` is fine inside TS string literals.
- No double spaces. No trailing commas in prose.
- Number + unit: `2 min.`, `5 val.`, `35 promptai`. Always a non-breaking space if HTML allows.

### Grammar traps to check

- Agent participles must agree with "Tu" (singular): `Prieš naudodamas...` (m.) — pick masculine generic for executive copy unless audience is explicitly female. Avoid plural `naudodami`.
- "veiks" (will operate) ≠ "paveiks" (will affect). EN "will affect" → LT `paveiks`.
- Word order: place the subject before the participle phrase. `DI, prijungtas prie neaiškaus proceso, atskleidžia...` ✓ rather than `Pridėtas DI prie...`.

## English Standard

### Voice

- Sentence case for headings and CTAs: `Download Max Value Kit`, not `Download Max Value KIT` or `Download max value kit`.
- Active voice. `The kit returns a decision-ready output` ✓ over `A decision-ready output is returned by the kit` ✗.
- Cut hedges: `helps you to`, `aims to`, `tries to`. State the outcome.
- Numbers under 10 spelled out only in body prose; in metric chips use digits (`2min`, `35`, `7`).

### Vocabulary

| Prefer | Avoid |
|---|---|
| decision, trade-off, risk, owner | insight, synergy, leverage (as a noun) |
| executive, leadership team | C-suite, leadership cadre |
| operating kit | playbook (overused) |
| safety check | guardrails (when speaking to CEOs) |
| install the system | onboard the system |

### Punctuation

- Em dash `—` (no spaces) for emphatic asides: `Decision first — every prompt points to an owner.`
- Oxford comma in lists of three or more.
- Sentence ends with one period only; no `..` or `...` unless quoting.

## Bilingual Alignment Rule

When you change one section in `src/content/copy.ts`, update the matching keys in the other language in the same commit. Do not leave a mixed-language deploy.

## Audit Checklist (run before claiming "done")

When asked to audit Lithuanian copy:

- [ ] No `kite\b` matches in the `lt` block of `copy.ts` (formal imperatives gone).
- [ ] No `jūsų`, `norite`, `galite`, `turite`.
- [ ] No `\bAI\b` in the `lt` block.
- [ ] No leftover English nouns mid-sentence (`support`, `account`, `meeting room` etc.).
- [ ] All Lithuanian vowels carry their diacritics.
- [ ] Buttons stay infinitive; section copy uses "Tu".
- [ ] EN and LT counterparts still describe the same idea.

When asked to audit English copy:

- [ ] No beginner-AI vocabulary.
- [ ] Headings in sentence case.
- [ ] No passive voice on key value statements.
- [ ] Each prompt category description names a decision, risk, trade-off, or next action.

After substantive copy edits, run `npm run build` and add a `CHANGELOG.md` entry under the current date.
